properties.documentation: Initial investigation shows fault is present, error waiting to be included in release cycle and to be assigned to resource.
The fix is released into the tagged build.
The fix must pass the unit test and/or can no longer be reproduced.
Claimed to be fixed and ready for code check by peer. Checked into forked code repository.
The change is merged into the code baseline. Repository tag at this stage is the one which will be used NEXT i.e. the tag for the build where this fix will appear.
New error reported and ready for processing.

Duplicate OR No fault found Can occur during initial analysis, or afterwards when further work by engineer determines alternative cause e.g. incorrect user operation (in which case the error becomes one of documentation).
Also should check that test description has been done and any supporting documentation amended, before passing review. Issue a pull request to the main codebase.
States other than Closed, Integrated, Fixed or Rejected, may transition to Suspended.
Assigned for fixing.
